title: Misogyny Much?
body:
Game of Thrones fans are ecstatic about the female characters in the show. At the beginning, these women were naive and didn’t know what they wanted exactly. At the beginning, some of them were abused by their own husbands or powerful people around them. Even worse, they were raped and had to live with their traumatic experiences. But at the end, these women learned that they were valuable and started to become leaders. Yes, they are flawed, but they experienced so much trauma that they learned from their stupid mistakes. Now here, these women have become strong, independent, resilient and intelligent. Despite that they were alone, they observed on how to adapt to their environment and picked up skills in order to survive. Some of these women were great fighters (such as Arya, Brienne, Ygritte and Yara) but others relied on strategy (Margaery, Olenna and Lyanna) and some were powerful (Cersei, Daenerys and Melisandre)

Whilst all these women receive praise, Sansa Stark (a girl who was naive but learned from her mistakes, who went through rape and abuse, who learned to adapt to the game of thrones, who helped Jon win the battle of the bastards and who executed two men that tormented her) is someone who receives NOTHING but pure hatred
